Theoretical Implications We set out to analyze the creation of a social problem by using the model
developed by Mauss (1975), a framework that stipulates the emergence of public concern prior to governmental actions. We were interested in explaining an apparent discrepancy between public and political fervor over the drug issue in 1986, and objective data that indicated no significant increases in the consumption of illicit drugs. We found some support for this model, albeit with important modifications.
It is apparent from the history of this problem that an incipiency stage existed for the new war on drugs. While public opinion polls just prior to the "creation" of the drug problem found a very small proportion of respondents identifying

